<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1764: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-20T15:00:00-04:00">May 20, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>104. The Colombian Minister has here received the following telegram,
                            dated May 20, from President Olaya which is repeated for your
                            confidential information: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Although the United Press from Lima announces settlement Leticia
                                    question, no official notice has been received from Geneva but
                                    on the contrary it has been announced that García Calderón
                                    wishes to present new modifications to the League formula, which
                                    are inacceptable.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>